				<p><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I acknowledge the<lb/> receipt of yours <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Inst. and<lb/> on making <sic>enquiries</sic> find that<lb/> <persName>Mr. Simons</persName> paid your agent<lb/> <persName>Mr. Rubenstein</persName> in <date>January<lb/> 1857</date>&#8212;two years subscription<lb/> to the Occident to <date>March 57</date>.<lb/> and at the same time paid<lb/> &#36;8.00 for the Bible.  <persName>Mr. R Hale</persName><lb/> on examining his accounts<lb/> that he rendered you a statement<lb/> <date>March 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> of these receipts<lb/> and remitted you &#36;25.50 amount</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>collected at that time<lb/> Please make a correct<lb/> recount &#38; oblige Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">H. Simons</persName>.</p>
				<p>The Bible is not gilt edged<lb/> or Russia binding</p>
				<p><placeName>22. Mansfield Place</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>W. 51<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Street</placeName></p>
